<p><a href="/people/wang_l/">Lixin Wang</a>, former member of the EcoHydrology Lab, was recently interview to discuss his work on the effects of drought on global production of legumes. <!--more-->According to Lixin: “Our results could facilitate the development and selection of existing legume species, as well as better management for drought-prone regions by testing whether these species become more or less sensitive to climate variations, particularly drought.”</p>

<p> </p>

<p>You can see the interview <a href="http://news.iupui.edu/releases/2015/06/legumes-drought-research-wang.shtml" target="_blank">HERE</a> and the original article <a href="http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0127401" target="_blank">HERE</a>.</p>
